description: Rezoning of 10511 Lassam Road from the “Single Detached RS1/E” Zone to the “Single Detached (RS2/B)” Zone to permit the property to be subdivided to create two single-family lots with access from Lassam Road. Each proposed lot will be approximately 12.6 m (41 ft.) wide and approximately 575 m² (6,189.25 ft²) in area.

behalf: 1303287 B.C. Ltd. (Balraj Singh Sanghera and Rajbir Kaur Chatha)
description: Rezoning of 11831/11833 Seabrook Crescent from the “Single Detached (RS1/E)” zone to the “Single Detached (RS2/B)” zone in order to permit the property to be subdivided into two single-family lots, each with vehicle access from Seabrook Crescent. The proposed subdivision plan and draft site plan are provided in Attachment 2.

behalf: Cliff Chun and Kai Shen Hsiung of 1296168 BC Ltd. and Yi Jen Wang and Kai Shen Hsiung of Terra West Properties Ltd.
description: The applicant wants to rezone the area from the 'Single Detached (RS1/E)' zone to the 'Low Density Townhouses (RTL4)' zone to permit the development of nine townhouse units, with vehicle access from No. 1 Road.

behalf: Thomas Mau Shing Ng, Ling Y Ha, Shui Ting Chua
description: The applicant is proposing to rezone the subject site and subdivide it into two single-family lots, each with a secondary suite, with access from Bonavista Gate. The proposed subdivision plan and site plan are provided in Attachment 2. The existing duplex (two-family) dwelling will be demolished prior to subdivision. The existing two-family dwelling is owner-occupied and does not contain any secondary suites. The proposed development is consistent with the Official Community Plan and Steveston Area Plan. The redevelopment must meet the requirements of the Richmond Flood Plain Designation and Protection Bylaw 8204. The applicant has worked with staff to modify the building envelope to enable retention of trees on site at the front and rear of the property.

Rezoning of 3300 Granville Avenue from “Single Detached (RS1/E)” zone to “Single Detached (RS2/B)” zone to allow the property to be subdivided into two single-family lots, each with a one bedroom secondary suite. Existing single-family dwelling to be demolished prior to subdivision. Vehicle access proposed to be from Granville Avenue.

The rezoning application is for the development of 30 townhouse units with seven secondary suites and a right-in/right-out vehicle access from Steveston Highway. The proposed density is 0.65 floor area ratio (FAR). The site layout includes 12 two-storey units and 18 three-storey units in ten townhouse clusters. Seven secondary suites and five accessible units are included in this proposal.

Rezoning of 7300 St. Albans Road from “Single Detached (RS1/E)” zone to “High Density Townhouses (RTH1)” zone to permit the development of four townhouse units with one secondary suite. The proposed development provides for a total of four three-storey townhouse units and one secondary suite, with a contribution at a rate of $0.34 per buildable square foot for future City Community Planning studies.

To rezone 2231-2247 East 41st Avenue from R1-1 (Residential Inclusive) District to RR-2B (Residential Rental) to permit the development of a five-storey rental building. A floor space ratio (FSR) of 2.20 and height of 16.8 m (55 ft.) are proposed.

To rezone 6470 Larch Street from R1-1 (Residential Inclusive) District to RR-2B (Residential Rental) District, to permit the development of a five-storey secured market rental building. A floor space ratio (FSR) of 2.20 and height of 16.8 m (55 ft.) are proposed.

To rezone the area to permit the development of a six-storey, 162-unit Community Care Facility with a floor space ratio (FSR) of 3.87 and a height of 27.5 m (90 ft.) with additional height for a rooftop amenity.

To rezone 848 Seymour Street from DD (Downtown) District to CD-1 (Comprehensive Development) District, to permit the development of a 30-storey hotel. A floor space ratio (FSR) of 17.67 and a height of 97.7 m (321 ft.) and are proposed.

applicant: DIALOG BC Architecture Engineering Interior Design Planning Inc.
behalf: Lu'ma Native Housing Society, ALT Commercial Housing Society
description: To rezone 1710-1730 East Pender Street from RM-4 and RM-4N (Residential) Districts to CD-1 (Comprehensive Development) District, to permit the development of an 18-storey mixed-use building containing 191 social housing units, including six live-work units, and ground floor commercial space. A floor space ratio (FSR) of 5.58 and a height of 60.8 m (199 ft.) with additional height for a rooftop amenity space are proposed.
To rezone 692 West 30th Avenue from R1-1 (Residential Inclusive) District to RM-8A (Multiple Dwelling) District, to permit a townhouse development with a maximum floor space ratio (FSR) of 1.20.
To rezone 688 West 29th Avenue from R1-1 (Residential Inclusive) District to RM-8A (Multiple Dwelling) District, to permit a townhouse development with a maximum floor space ratio (FSR) of 1.20.

behalf: Mosaic Flora and Fauna Holdings Ltd.
description: To rezone 4711-4787 Cambie Street from R1-1 (Residential Inclusive) District to CD-1 (Comprehensive Development) District, to permit the development of two six-storey, strata-titled residential buildings. A floor space ratio (FSR) of 2.65 and a height of 23.6 m (77.4 ft.) and are proposed. The development includes 114 strata-titled residential units.

To rezone the area from R1-1 (Residential Inclusive) District to CD-1 (Comprehensive Development) District, to permit the development of two six-storey residential buildings consisting of 146 secured-market rental units, of which five units would be below-market rental. A floor space ratio (FSR) of 2.88 and a height of 20.7 m (68 ft.) with additional height for a rooftop amenity and mechanical appurtenances are proposed.

behalf: Strata Corporation of 3352-3386 Vanness Avenue Strata Plan LMS992 and the registered owners of the strata lots in Strata Plan LMS922, and the registered owner of 3347 Clive Avenue
description: Rezoning of the consolidated lands at 3352-3386 Vanness Avenue and 3347 Clive Avenue from CD-1(201) (Comprehensive Development) District and CD-1(218) (Comprehensive Development) District to CD-1 (Comprehensive Development) District, respectively, to increase the maximum floor space ratio (FSR) from 1.45 and 0.6 respectively to 11.38 and the maximum building height from 35.5 m (120 ft.) and 11.9 m (39 ft.) respectively to 104.9 m (344 ft.), to permit a mixed-use development with 30-storey (west tower) and 33-storey (east tower) buildings connected with a six-storey podium, with 679 secured rental units, of which 10% of the residential floor area will be secured at below market rents, commercial uses on the ground floor and a 37-space turn-key childcare facility for City ownership

The rezoning application is to rezone the lands from IC-2 (Industrial) District to CD-1 (Comprehensive Development) District to increase the maximum floor space ratio (FSR) from 3.0 to 6.27 and the maximum building height from 18.3 m (60 ft.) to 79.3 m (260 ft.) with mechanical appurtenances permitted up to a maximum of 3.6 m (12 ft.) above the permitted building height, to permit the development of a 25-storey, mixed-use building containing 210 secured-rental housing units, of which 20% of the residential floor area will be secured as below-market rental units, with commercial space on the ground floor.

The rezoning application is to rezone the lands from RM-5A (Residential) District to CD-1 (Comprehensive Development) District, to increase the maximum floor space ratio (FSR) from 2.2 to 11.9 and the maximum building height from 18.30 m (60 ft.) to 91.44 m (300 ft.) to permit the development of a 32-storey residential building containing 269 secured-rental units of which 20% of the residential floor area will be secured as below-market rental units.

The rezoning application is to rezone the lands from R1-1 (Residential Inclusive) District to CD-1 (Comprehensive Development) District to increase the floor space ratio (FSR) from 0.70 to 0.75 and the building height from 11.5 m (38 ft.) to 13.8 m (45 ft.), to permit 28 secured market rental residential units.

To rezone the area from R1-1 (Residential Inclusive) District to CD-1 (Comprehensive Development) District, to permit the development of two six-storey residential buildings consisting of 146 secured-market rental units, of which five units would be below-market rental. A floor space ratio (FSR) of 2.88 and a height of 20.7 m (68 ft.) with additional height for a rooftop amenity and mechanical appurtenances are proposed.
